channel.title: Vistex V7 Help!
channel.description: Hi, ive been developing Vistex V7 for a few days now and i noticed every one in a while a random message saying something like [Vistex] First player to say 453ghg575 will receive 56 sharks or something along those lines. I've had no problems with anything other than this. Please could anyone tell me how to edit/delete this. Thanks

item.title: Vistex V7 Help!
item.dc:creator: @PvPXile PvPXile
item.description:
@PvPXile wrote:

mgl:

If your own windows 7 this should be fairly easy. Open your java files and use the folder searcher to find the keywords like; “[Vistex]” or “453ghg575”. One a java files pops up on the searcher, pen it and use CTRL+F and search for the same keyword over again, if you find the function sending that random message out. Delete it.

Thanks but im on XP so i dont think the inner file find function works…
